<abstract>
<p>This article adopts a strategic management approach to addressing the issue of how to achieve both corporate profitability and corporate social responsibility in dealing with <italic>Guanxi</italic> in the Chinese business context. It argues that environment scanning, strategy formulation, strategy implementation and strategy evaluation and control should be the key components of strategic management of <italic>Guanxi</italic>. The article proposes a practical framework for managing <italic>Guanxi</italic> strategically in the emerging China market, and illustrates the framework with cases in the real world.</p>
</abstract>
